{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, Standalone devices were increasingly being used due to their greater storage capacity and better quality.",
    "They were replacing Cardboard in Passive experiences and competing with Desktop 6DOF in all other interactions.",
    "• Unity was the most widely used videogame engine for developing iVR applications (37.5%).",
    "Unreal Engine had replaced Source after it was discontinued.",
    "Many departments purchased the applications (14.8%) or outsourced development, due to the lack of capacity to produce iVR applications."
  ]
}